<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reave" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reave</orth> (impf. and partic. <emph>reft</emph>) 1) to bereave, to deprive; with <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>--s his son of life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 766" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 766</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>would have reft the fishers of their prey,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 116</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 116</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.233" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 103</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>refts,</emph> M. Edd. <emph>reft'st</emph>). <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 84</bibl>.<lb />2) to take away: <cit><quote>since he himself is reft from her by death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1174" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1174</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>